===Etymology===
From {{etyl|goh|de}} {{term|sehan|lang=goh}}, from {{proto|Germanic|sehwanan|lang=de}}, from {{proto|Indo-European|sekʷ-|to see|lang=de}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈzeːən/|lang=de}}
* {{audio|De-at-sehen.ogg|audio (Austria)}}
* {{homophones|Seen}}

===Verb===
{{de-verb-strong|class=5|sieht|sah|gesehen}}

# {{intransitive}} to [[see]]; to [[look]]; to have sight
#: ''auf etwas '''sehen''''' — “to look at something”
#: ''nach etwas '''sehen''''' — “to look for something”
# {{intransitive|with “[[nach]] ...”|lang=de}} to take care (of something or someone); to make (something) happen; to [[see]] (to something); to [[look]] (after someone)
# {{transitive}} to [[see]] (something); to [[view]]; to [[watch]]; to [[observe]]; to look at
# {{transitive}} to [[notice]]; to [[perceive]]; to [[realize]]
# {{reflexive|_|with a plural subject|or|transitive}} to [[meet]]; to go to [[see]]

